[Name] LatencyTop
[Summary] A tool aimed at identifying system latencies 
[Description] LatencyTOP is a Linux* tool for software developers (both kernel and userspace), aimed at identifying where in the system latency is happening, and what kind of operation/action is causing the latency to happen so that the code can be changed to avoid the worst latency hiccups.  
[License] GPL v2 
[Homepage] http://www.latencytop.org 
